description:
- Taste: yay
- Value: ranges depending on order
- Service: ok
- Ambiance: ok

// Tofu soup: 4 stars: $11.95 pre-tax for chicken soft tofu soup with rice cakes, banchan and purple rice. Pleased with the variety of the mushrooms!

// Banchan: 3 stars. Bean sprouts were good but wasn't a fan of the kimchi due to the heavy radish or daikon flavor. Broccoli, and a few others came with -- nothing special

Many of the menu options felt a bit pricey (seafood pancake entree at $16, or the $2 for extra purple rice) but this place is mom and pop, which I'm a fan of.

** Tip: Very small place, tea is free and there's a free gyoza upon checkin! 

// TLDR: Overall, good if you're in the area but I wouldn't go out of your way to come.
